Regarding the influence of the functionality of the crosslinker on the changes in the SSPCMs endothermic enthalpy, the degree of latent heat for both MDI- and HDI-based SSPCM followed the order; CO < COM < COT. Studies have revealed several factors that influence the SSPCM phase transition properties, including soft segment content by weight, crystalline state of the soft segments, and steric hindrance of the crosslinking points. With an increase in the functionality of the crosslinker, the synthesized SSPCM can accommodate more PEG, thereby increasing the latent heat storage capacity. For better understanding of the phase transition properties of the SSPCMs on the basis of the functionality of the crosslinker, the relative latent heat efficiency was calculated using the following equation:η=ΔHm.SSPCMΔHm.PEG×ωPEG×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
